    {
      "text": "Robo Pit (ロボピット) is a 1996 fighting game for PlayStation and Sega Saturn by Japanese video game company Altron. It is a 3D arena fighter involving robots whereby players build a robot and compete against other robots to the top. It was originally released on January 13, 1996, and was published internationally by Kokopeli Digital Studios.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "Robo Pit (ロボピット) est un jeu vidéo de combat développé et édité par Altron, sorti en 1996 sur Saturn et PlayStation.\nIl a pour suite Robo Pit 2.",
